{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":758,"text":"We're going to begin in 1964."},{"time":4049,"text":"Bob Dylan is 23 years old, and his career"},{"time":7022,"text":"is just reaching its pinnacle."},{"time":9183,"text":"He's been christened the voice of a generation,"},{"time":11624,"text":"and he's churning out classic songs"},{"time":14084,"text":"at a seemingly impossible rate,"},{"time":16047,"text":"but there's a small minority of dissenters, and they claim"},{"time":20498,"text":"that Bob Dylan is stealing other people's songs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24237,"text":"2004. Brian Burton, aka Danger Mouse,"},{"time":28377,"text":"takes the Beatles' \"White Album,\""},{"time":30290,"text":"combines it with Jay-Z's \"The Black Album\""},{"time":32067,"text":"to create \"The Grey Album.\""},{"time":33891,"text":"\"The Grey Album\" becomes an immediate sensation online,"},{"time":35810,"text":"and the Beatles' record company sends out countless"},{"time":38570,"text":"cease-and-desist letters for \"unfair competition"},{"time":41810,"text":"and dilution of our valuable property.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":45691,"text":"Now, \"The Grey Album\" is a remix."},{"time":47683,"text":"It is new media created from old media."},{"time":50080,"text":"It was made using these three techniques:"},{"time":52665,"text":"copy, transform and combine."},{"time":55907,"text":"It's how you remix. You take existing songs,"},{"time":57829,"text":"you chop them up, you transform the pieces,"},{"time":59549,"text":"you combine them back together again,"},{"time":61389,"text":"and you've got a new song, but that new song"},{"time":63366,"text":"is clearly comprised of old songs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66100,"text":"But I think these aren't just the components of remixing."},{"time":69413,"text":"I think these are the basic elements of all creativity."},{"time":72457,"text":"I think everything is a remix,"},{"time":74268,"text":"and I think this is a better way to conceive of creativity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78959,"text":"All right, let's head back to 1964, and let's hear"},{"time":81952,"text":"where some of Dylan's early songs came from."},{"time":84973,"text":"We'll do some side-by-side comparisons here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86850,"text":"All right, this first song you're going to hear"},{"time":88056,"text":"is \"Nottamun Town.\" It's a traditional folk tune."},{"time":90470,"text":"After that, you'll hear Dylan's \"Masters of War.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":93058,"text":"Jean Ritchie: ♫ In Nottamun Town, not a soul would look out, ♫\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":97958,"text":"♫ not a soul would look up, not a soul would look down. ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":104556,"text":"Bob Dylan: ♫ Come you masters of war, ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":108830,"text":"♫ you that build the big guns, you that build the death planes, ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":117435,"text":"♫ You that build all the bombs. ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":120504,"text":"Kirby Ferguson: Okay, so that's the same basic melody"},{"time":122426,"text":"and overall structure. This next one is \"The Patriot Game,\""},{"time":125585,"text":"by Dominic Behan. Alongside that,"},{"time":127577,"text":"you're going to hear \"With God on Our Side,\" by Dylan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129851,"text":"Dominic Behan: ♫ Come all ye young rebels, ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":135109,"text":"♫ and list while I sing, ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":139639,"text":"♫ for the love of one's land is a terrible thing. ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":147851,"text":"BD: ♫ Oh my name it is nothin', ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":153663,"text":"♫ my age it means less, ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":158191,"text":"♫ the country I come from is called the Midwest. ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":165010,"text":"KF: Okay, so in this case, Dylan admits"},{"time":166636,"text":"he must have heard \"The Patriot Game,\" he forgot about it,"},{"time":169076,"text":"then when the song kind of bubbled back up"},{"time":170635,"text":"in his brain, he just thought it was his song."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172946,"text":"Last one, this is \"Who's Going To Buy You Ribbons,\""},{"time":174178,"text":"another traditional folk tune."},{"time":175738,"text":"Alongside that is \"Don't Think Twice, It's All Right.\""},{"time":178035,"text":"This one's more about the lyric."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179860,"text":"Paul Clayton: ♫ It ain't no use to sit and sigh now, ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":186751,"text":"♫ darlin', and it ain't no use to sit and cry now. ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":194615,"text":"BD: ♫ It ain’t no use to sit and wonder why, babe, ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":200560,"text":"♫ if you don't know by now, ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":204212,"text":"♫ and it ain't no use to sit and wonder why, babe, ♫\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":209603,"text":"♫ it'll never do somehow. ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":212490,"text":"KF: Okay, now, there's a lot of these."},{"time":214762,"text":"It's been estimated that two thirds of the melodies"},{"time":216776,"text":"Dylan used in his early songs were borrowed."},{"time":219319,"text":"This is pretty typical among folk singers."},{"time":221175,"text":"Here's the advice of Dylan's idol, Woody Guthrie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223538,"text":"\"The worlds are the important thing."},{"time":225068,"text":"Don't worry about tunes. Take a tune,"},{"time":226900,"text":"sing high when they sing low,"},{"time":228576,"text":"sing fast when they sing slow, and you've got a new tune.\""},{"time":231784,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":235781,"text":"And that's, that's what Guthrie did right here,"},{"time":237728,"text":"and I'm sure you all recognize the results."},{"time":240335,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":246252,"text":"We know this tune, right? We know it?"},{"time":248647,"text":"Actually you don't."},{"time":250060,"text":"That is \"When the World's on Fire,\" a very old melody,"},{"time":252744,"text":"in this case performed by the Carter Family."},{"time":255005,"text":"Guthrie adapted it into \"This Land Is Your Land.\""},{"time":257683,"text":"So, Bob Dylan, like all folk singers, he copied melodies,"},{"time":262003,"text":"he transformed them, he combined them with new lyrics"},{"time":264725,"text":"which were frequently their own concoction"},{"time":267122,"text":"of previous stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269383,"text":"Now, American copyright and patent laws run counter"},{"time":273046,"text":"to this notion that we build on the work of others."},{"time":275769,"text":"Instead, these laws and laws around the world"},{"time":278436,"text":"use the rather awkward analogy of property."},{"time":282158,"text":"Now, creative works may indeed be kind of like property,"},{"time":284601,"text":"but it's property that we're all building on,"},{"time":286910,"text":"and creations can only take root and grow"},{"time":289399,"text":"once that ground has been prepared."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292115,"text":"Henry Ford once said, \"I invented nothing new."},{"time":294961,"text":"I simply assembled the discoveries of other men"},{"time":296964,"text":"behind whom were centuries of work."},{"time":299551,"text":"Progress happens when all the factors that make for it"},{"time":301934,"text":"are ready and then it is inevitable.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":305964,"text":"2007. The iPhone makes it debut."},{"time":310509,"text":"Apple undoubtedly brings this innovation to us early,"},{"time":313176,"text":"but its time was approaching because its core technology"},{"time":315673,"text":"had been evolving for decades."},{"time":317719,"text":"That's multi-touch, controlling a device"},{"time":319701,"text":"by touching its display."},{"time":321478,"text":"Here is Steve Jobs introducing multi-touch"},{"time":323897,"text":"and making a rather foreboding joke."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326137,"text":"Steve Jobs: And we have invented a new technology"},{"time":328940,"text":"called multi-touch."},{"time":331200,"text":"You can do multi-fingered gestures on it,"},{"time":333653,"text":"and boy have we patented it. (Laughter)"},{"time":337264,"text":"KF: Yes. And yet, here is multi-touch in action."},{"time":341430,"text":"This is at TED, actually, about a year earlier."},{"time":343451,"text":"This is Jeff Han, and, I mean, that's multi-touch."},{"time":345919,"text":"It's the same animal, at least."},{"time":347670,"text":"Let's hear what Jeff Han has to say about this"},{"time":349437,"text":"newfangled technology."},{"time":351263,"text":"Jeff Han: Multi-touch sensing isn't anything --"},{"time":353431,"text":"isn't completely new. I mean, people like Bill Buxton"},{"time":355637,"text":"have been playing around with it in the '80s."},{"time":357286,"text":"The technology, you know, isn't the most exciting thing here"},{"time":360485,"text":"right now other than probably its newfound accessibility."},{"time":363547,"text":"KF: So he's pretty frank about it not being new."},{"time":365480,"text":"So it's not multi-touch as a whole that's patented."},{"time":368023,"text":"It's the small parts of it that are,"},{"time":370160,"text":"and it's in these small details where"},{"time":371464,"text":"we can clearly see patent law contradicting its intent:"},{"time":374582,"text":"to promote the progress of useful arts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377743,"text":"Here is the first ever slide-to-unlock."},{"time":380927,"text":"That is all there is to it. Apple has patented this."},{"time":383796,"text":"It's a 28-page software patent, but I will summarize"},{"time":386608,"text":"what it covers. Spoiler alert: Unlocking your phone"},{"time":390544,"text":"by sliding an icon with your finger. (Laughter)"},{"time":393481,"text":"I'm only exaggerating a little bit. It's a broad patent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396498,"text":"Now, can someone own this idea?"},{"time":399347,"text":"Now, back in the '80s, there were no software patents,"},{"time":401777,"text":"and it was Xerox that pioneered the graphical user interface."},{"time":404938,"text":"What if they had patented pop-up menus,"},{"time":407856,"text":"scrollbars, the desktop with icons that look like folders"},{"time":412280,"text":"and sheets of paper?"},{"time":414267,"text":"Would a young and inexperienced Apple"},{"time":416616,"text":"have survived the legal assault from a much larger"},{"time":419485,"text":"and more mature company like Xerox?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":423565,"text":"Now, this idea that everything is a remix might sound"},{"time":426012,"text":"like common sense until you're the one getting remixed."},{"time":430139,"text":"For example ..."},{"time":431789,"text":"SJ: I mean, Picasso had a saying."},{"time":433028,"text":"He said, \"Good artists copy. Great artists steal.\""},{"time":436585,"text":"And we have, you know,"},{"time":438907,"text":"always been shameless about stealing great ideas."},{"time":442035,"text":"KF: Okay, so that's in '96. Here's in 2010."},{"time":443933,"text":"\"I'm going to destroy Android because it's a stolen product.\""},{"time":446842,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":448384,"text":"\"I'm willing to go thermonuclear war on this.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":452023,"text":"Okay, so in other words, great artists steal, but not from me."},{"time":455527,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":457878,"text":"Now, behavioral economists might refer to this sort of thing as loss aversion"},{"time":461486,"text":"We have a strong predisposition towards protecting"},{"time":463705,"text":"what we feel is ours."},{"time":465634,"text":"We have no such aversion towards copying"},{"time":467552,"text":"what other people have, because we do that nonstop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470285,"text":"So here's the sort of equation we're looking at."},{"time":472760,"text":"We've got laws that fundamentally treat creative works as property,"},{"time":475417,"text":"plus massive rewards or settlements"},{"time":478202,"text":"in infringement cases, plus huge legal fees"},{"time":480399,"text":"to protect yourself in court,"},{"time":482062,"text":"plus cognitive biases against perceived loss."},{"time":485566,"text":"And the sum looks like this."},{"time":487709,"text":"That is the last four years of lawsuits"},{"time":490532,"text":"in the realm of smartphones."},{"time":493098,"text":"Is this promoting the progress of useful arts?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":498869,"text":"1983. Bob Dylan is 42 years old, and his time"},{"time":504637,"text":"in the cultural spotlight is long since past."},{"time":507963,"text":"He records a song called \"Blind Willie McTell,\""},{"time":510572,"text":"named after the blues singer, and the song"},{"time":512758,"text":"is a voyage through the past, through a much darker time,"},{"time":516428,"text":"but a simpler one, a time when musicians like Willie McTell"},{"time":519578,"text":"had few illusions about what they did."},{"time":522098,"text":"\"I jump 'em from other writers"},{"time":524348,"text":"but I arrange 'em my own way.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":526913,"text":"I think this is mostly what we do."},{"time":528630,"text":"Our creativity comes from without, not from within."},{"time":531996,"text":"We are not self-made. We are dependent on one another,"},{"time":534917,"text":"and admitting this to ourselves isn't an embrace"},{"time":537742,"text":"of mediocrity and derivativeness."},{"time":540576,"text":"It's a liberation from our misconceptions,"},{"time":543209,"text":"and it's an incentive to not expect so much from ourselves"},{"time":546292,"text":"and to simply begin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549027,"text":"Thank you so much. It was an honor to be here."},{"time":551977,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":554754,"text":"Thank you. Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":558138,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}